msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_djc_4.md:45
msgid "Hardware controls"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_djc_4.md:48
msgid ""
"The **Master** and **Mic Level** are hardware controls and interact directly"
" with the integrated sound card and are not mapped to Mixxx."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_djc_4.md:51
msgid ""
"The {ref}`gain staging documentation <djing-gain-staging>` explains how to "
"set your levels properly when using Mixxx."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_djc_4.md:53
msgid "Mapping description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_djc_4.md:56
msgid ""
"The knobs for {hwlabel}`MASTER LEVEL`, {hwlabel}`MIC LEVEL` and the "
"{hwlabel}`MIC ON/OFF` switch are controlling the hardware mixer of the "
"built-in audio interface. Hence, turning the knobs will not change values in"
" the Mixxx {term}`GUI` and you’ll need to set the Mixxx knobs to their "
"default values when using the controller."
msgstr ""

